<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;404.  Disability, Sexuality, and Health.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Explores how political, social, and cultural systems as well as historical contexts shape understandings and experiences of disability, sexuality, and health. Course Information: Same as <a href="/search/?P=GWS%20404" title="GWS&#160;404" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'GWS 404');">GWS&#160;404</a>. 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): Junior standing or above; or consent of the instructor.<br />
