<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;406.  Disability and Work.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Explores the complex relationship between disability and work within the U.S. Student will learn about debates and interventions surrounding the role, ability, and capability of people with disabilities to work. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): Junior standing or above; or consent of the instructor. Recommended background: <a href="/search/?P=DHD%20101" title="DHD&#160;101" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DHD 101');">DHD&#160;101</a> and an additional 6 credit hours of  coursework in Disability and Human Development.<br />
