<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;407.  Cultural Politics of Disability and Health.  3 or 4 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Examines the construction and circulation of knowledge about bodies, health, medicine and impairment from a disability studies perspective. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): Junior standing or above; or consent of the instructor. Recommended background: <a href="/search/?P=DHD%20101" title="DHD&#160;101" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DHD 101');">DHD&#160;101</a> and an additional six credit hours of DHD coursework.<br />
