<p class="courseblockdesc">
Provides an overview of varying approaches to the study of disability through the life course from early childhood to adulthood and aging. Course Information: 3 undergraduate hours. 4 graduate hours. Prerequisite(s): Junior standing or above; or consent of the instructor. Recommended background: <a href="/search/?P=DHD%20101" title="DHD&#160;101" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DHD 101');">DHD&#160;101</a> and an additional six credit hours of coursework in Disability and Human Development.<br />
