<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;440.  Introduction to Assistive Technology: Principles and Practice.  3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Principles and exemplary practice of assistive technology used by individuals with disabilities, including augmentative communication, seating, mobility, computer access, environmental control, home modifications, and worksite modifications.  Course Information: Prerequisite(s): Graduate standing or consent of the instructor.  Recommended background:  Undergraduate enrolled in health sciences, education, or engineering and working professionals seeking to develop assistive technology as an area of concentration.<br />
</p>
