<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;514.  Ethical Issues in Disability.  2-3 hours.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Examines contemporary ethical issues affecting the lives of persons with disabilities and disability professionals. Critiques the application of ethical principles to problems of genetics, treatment decisions and competency. Course Information: Extensive computer use required.<br />
