<p class="courseblockdesc">
Ethical theories and ethical decision-making are examined from an interdisciplinary disability studies perspective in relation to people with disabilities. Topics include assisted suicide, de-institutionalization, and genetic discrimination. Course Information: Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=DHD%20514" title="DHD&#160;514" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DHD 514');">DHD&#160;514</a> or consent of the instructor.<br />
