<p class="courseblocktitle"><strong>DHD&#160;557.  Manual Wheelchair Technology.  1 hour.</strong></p>
<p class="courseblockdesc">
Focuses on manual wheelchair designs and components for use by children and adults with physical disabilities. Performance adjustments, transportation standards and securement systems, funding and related research are covered. Course Information: Taught online over a consecutive five-week period. Prerequisite(s): <a href="/search/?P=DHD%20556" title="DHD&#160;556" class="bubblelink code" onclick="return showCourse(this, 'DHD 556');">DHD&#160;556</a>; and consent of the instructor. Recommended background: Physical Therapy, Occupational Therapy, Speech-Language Pathology, Special Education, Engineering.<br />
</p>
